==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Elaborative
<hw>E*lab"o*ra*tive</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <def>Serving or
tending to elaborate; constructing with labor and minute attention to
details.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><cs><col><b>Elaborative faculty</b></col> <fld>(Metaph.)</fld>,
<cd>the intellectual power of discerning relations and of viewing
objects by means of, or in, relations; the discursive faculty;
thought.</cd></cs>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Elaborator</ent>⟦br⟧
